// Previous attempt extracted LHS conjuncts (e.g.
// `post1_netc.my_end_point() == pre_netc.my_end_point()`,
// `post1_netc.ok() <==> r1.0`) as standalone asserts. Those facts live
// only under the antecedent of the ensures-implication, so Verus
// (correctly) rejected them from `requires` alone. Drop that approach
// and instead emit only tautologies that line up the spec-fn / field
// view of each NetClient so z3 has the shape it needs.

// `View for NetClient` is a non-external_body `closed spec fn` whose body
// is the in-module record `NetClientView { history: self.history@,
// end_point: self.end_point }`. The next four asserts unfold that
// definition on both post-states (and pre_netc, symmetrically) so z3
// sees the connection between `post*_netc.view()` and the underlying
// fields. They are pure definitional truths — Verus can discharge them
// from the visible body of `view()` without any LHS hypothesis.
assert(pre_netc.view().history == pre_netc.history@);
assert(pre_netc.view().end_point == pre_netc.end_point);
assert(post1_netc.view().history == post1_netc.history@);
assert(post1_netc.view().end_point == post1_netc.end_point);
assert(post2_netc.view().history == post2_netc.history@);
assert(post2_netc.view().end_point == post2_netc.end_point);

// `View for LIoOp` is likewise a closed non-external_body spec fn that
// pattern-matches on the four LIoOp variants. The two asserts below
// unfold it on the Send branch — the only branch
// `send_log_entry_reflects_packet` allows — so that when r1.1@ /
// r2.1@ are Some, z3 sees `r*.1@.unwrap().view()` in terms of
// `LIoOpView::Send { s: r*.1@.unwrap().arrow_Send_s() }`.
assert(forall|e: NetEvent| e is Send ==>
    #[trigger] e.view() == LIoOpView::Send::<AbstractEndPoint, Seq<u8>> { s: e.arrow_Send_s() });

// Tautological reflexivity hint on the shared `cpacket@`, the only
// term that both runs' send_log_entry_reflects_packet axioms key on.
// This term is the bridge: each run forces
// `cpacket@ == abstractify_net_packet_to_sht_packet(event_i.arrow_Send_s())`,
// so z3 needs `cpacket@` to appear as a common trigger.
assert(cpacket@ == cpacket@);
